{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudstabbar"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"15.0","name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"unavailable":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS"},{"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"unavailable":false}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents10OUDSTabBarV","title":"OUDSTabBar","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTabBar"}],"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTabBar"}],"symbolKind":"struct"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"The Tab bar is a system navigation component with a position which can vary depending to the OS.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The tab bar can be found at the bottom of the screen for iOS. It can vary for iPadOS.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It allows users to switch between the sections of an app.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Each tab can be represented by a label, optionally paired with an icon, and maintains persistent visibility across top-level destinations.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar\/init(content:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar\/init(selected:count:content:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar\/init(selectedTab:count:content:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar\/body"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar\/View-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTabBar"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"Content"},{"kind":"text","text":"> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Content"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:7SwiftUI4ViewP","text":"View"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Navigations"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Appearances","type":"heading","text":"Appearances","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS 26 brings Liquid Glass, the new Apple look and feel which will prevent developers to define specific styles for some critical components like bars."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Because today the OUDS tab bar relies on native component and is not designed from scratch, some elements will look different between iOS 26 and older versions:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"background color of tab bar can be changed for iOS lower than 26"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"background color of tab bar does not change since iOS 26"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"normal \/ unselected tab item color can be changed for both image and text only for iOS lower than 26"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"with iOS 26 no token of color are applied on unselected \/ normal tab item because only the image will be changed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and not the text making theme not readable in dark color scheme"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition the badges colors will be the same and cannot be changed (except with token definition). These particular badges do not rely on "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBadge","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" component,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the native API is used instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because Liquid Glass is available since iOS 26, the tab bar will be liquified \/ glassified since this OS version, not before."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you use SF Symbols for images, if they exist their "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"fill"}]},{"type":"text","text":" variant will be automatically used in the tab bar (native behaviour)."}]},{"anchor":"Platform-considerations","type":"heading","text":"Platform considerations","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This component is tailored for iOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On iPadOS the tabs do not apply the fonts since iPadOS 18"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because macOS does not support UIKit and because UIKIt is used to define the style of the tab bar, there is not styling of the tab bar for macOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"visionOS with is specific UI does not apply colors on tab bars and things are glasssified"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component is not available for watchOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component is not available for tvOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Guidelines","type":"heading","text":"Guidelines","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS guidelines recommends to:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"limit when possible the number of items to 5"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"use both images and texts in tab bar items"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"use badges only when needed to avoid to have heavy tab bar"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"be sure the selected information is not only defined by the color of the tab; you may need to change the shape or the fill of the image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"if a badge must be displayed, prefer short texts. If the text is a decimal value greater than 99, prefer display “+99”"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"if decorative images are used for tab bar item, apply "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"template"}]},{"type":"text","text":" rendering mode on it to apply color on tabs"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Technical-constraints","type":"heading","text":"Technical constraints","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must use in your tab bar items images with "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"a size of 26 x 26"}]},{"type":"text","text":", otherwise rendering could be unaligned with Figma specifications"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because the component cannot compute the ideal width of the selected tab indicator (for iOS before 26 and iPadOS before 18), ideal width based on the tab bar item content,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this indicator is not displayed for iOS lower than 26 in landscape mode and iPadOS."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your tabs embedded in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTabBar"},{"type":"text","text":" do not contain texts but only images, add an accessibility label introducing the journey for this tab"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your tabs embedded in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTabBar"},{"type":"text","text":" display a badge (empty or with text), vocalize it in your tab to let users know what it is (unread messages, new things, etc)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by using accessibiltiy value"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"code":["    OUDSTabBar {","        SomeView()","            .tabItem {","                Label {","                    Text(\"Emails\") \/\/ The text is vocalized first","                        .accessibilityValue(\"5 unread emails\") \/\/ A value vocalized after the text","            } icon: {","                Image(systemName: \"mail\").accessibilityHidden(true)","            }","        }","        .badge(5) \/\/ The value you give to the badge","    }",""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Selection-of-tabs","type":"heading","text":"Selection of tabs","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For iOS lower than 26, a selected tab indicator can be displayed in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTabBar"},{"type":"text","text":" if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter is defined (to the number of tabs in the component)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectedTab"},{"type":"text","text":" binding value is equal to a given tag associated to a tab item."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise the indicator won’t appear; these parameters are mandatory to compute the location of the indicator."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This rule is only applied if selected tab indicator must be displayed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When the user taps a tab, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectedTab"},{"type":"text","text":" binding is updated automatically, keeping the parent view in sync."}]},{"anchor":"Technical-considerations","type":"heading","text":"Technical considerations","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to improve the Developer eXperience the current "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTabBar"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation lets users define their own tab items."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OUDS applies only appearances and styles on elements to prevent users to define raw data to assign to the component before being rendered like a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"picker"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thus users will need to add their own accessiiblity label if badges are used or also apply "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"template"}]},{"type":"text","text":" rendering mode on images if needed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thus it will be also possible to use Liquid Glass new API with animations and items stacking."}]},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","text":"Code samples","level":2},{"code":["    \/\/ Use the OUDS tab bar to wrap tab bar items and associated views","    \/\/ Item tagged 0 will be selected first, 3 tabs are embedded.","    \/\/ Image with size of 26 x 26","    @State private var selectedTab = 0","","    OUDSTabBar(selectedTab: $selectedTab, count: 3) {","","        \/\/ Add the views with the SwiftUI tab item and labels","        \/\/ No need to define colors, everything is done inside OUDSTabBar","        SomeView()","            .tabItem {","                Label(\"Label 1\", image: \"image_1\")","            }","            .tag(0) \/\/ Must match the selectedTab binding value","        OtherView()","            .tabItem {","                Label {","                    Text(\"Label 2\")","                } icon: {","                    Image(decorative: \"image_2\")","                        .renderingMode(.template) \/\/ Mandatory to apply color on selected item","                }","             }","            .tag(1) \/\/ Must be used for the selectedTab binding","        LastView()","            .tabItem {","                Label(\"Label 3\", image: \"image_3\")","            }","            .tag(2) \/\/ Must be used for the selectedTab binding","    }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","text":"Design documentation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-ios-tab-bar","isActive":true}]},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering","level":2},{"anchor":"Liquid-Glass","type":"heading","text":"Liquid Glass","level":3},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","text":"Orange","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Orange_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Orange_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_OrangeCompact_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_OrangeCompact_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading","text":"Sosh","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Sosh_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Sosh_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","text":"Wireframe","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Wireframe_light","type":"image"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Wireframe_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Without-Liquid-Glass","type":"heading","text":"Without Liquid Glass","level":3},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","text":"Orange","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_Orange_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_Orange_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_OrangeCompact_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_OrangeCompact_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading","text":"Sosh","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_Sosh_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_Sosh_dark"}]},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","text":"Wireframe","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_Wireframe_light"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tabBar_Wireframe_dark"}]},{"name":"Version","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.0.0 (Figma component design version)"}]}],"style":"note"},{"name":"Since","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.0.0"}]}],"style":"note"}]}],"references":{"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Orange_dark":{"identifier":"component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Orange_dark","alt":"A tab bar component in dark mode with Liquid Glass effect and Orange theme","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_tabBar_LiquidGlass_Orange_dark.png"}],"type":"image"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSTabBar":{"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudstabbar","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTabBar","title":"OUDSTabBar","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Tab bar is a system navigation component with a position which can vary depending to the OS."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The tab bar can be found at the bottom of the screen for iOS. It can vary for iPadOS."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It allows users to switch between the sections of an app."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Each tab can be represented by a label, optionally paired with an icon, and maintains persistent visibility across top-level destinations."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSTabBar","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSTabBar","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"component_tabBar_Wireframe_dark":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponen